item.text: Over the last 2 weeks, how often have you been bothered by any of the following problems? (Use “X” to indicate your answer)

options.display: SAMHSA-6 drinks / Never/Less than monthly/Monthly/Weekly/Daily/Almost daily

item.text: How often do you have a drink containing alcohol?

options.display: SAMHSA-drinks a day / 1 or 2/3 or 4/5 or 6/7 to 9/10 or more

item.text: How many standard drinks containing alcohol do you have on a typical day when drinking

options.display: SAMHSA-6 drinks / Never/Less than monthly/Monthly/Weekly/Daily/Almost daily

item.text: How often do you have six or more drinks on one occasion?

options.display: SAMHSA-6 drinks / Never/Less than monthly/Monthly/Weekly/Daily/Almost daily

item.text: During the past year, how often have you found that you were not able to stop drinking once you had started?

options.display: SAMHSA-6 drinks / Never/Less than monthly/Monthly/Weekly/Daily/Almost daily

item.text: During the past year, how often have you failed to do what was normally expected of you because of drinking?

options.display: SAMHSA-6 drinks / Never/Less than monthly/Monthly/Weekly/Daily/Almost daily

item.text: During the past year, how often have you needed a drink in the morning to get yourself going after a heavy drinking session?

options.display: SAMHSA-6 drinks / Never/Less than monthly/Monthly/Weekly/Daily/Almost daily

item.text: During the past year, how often have you had a feeling of guilt or remorse after drinking?

options.display: SAMHSA-6 drinks / Never/Less than monthly/Monthly/Weekly/Daily/Almost daily

item.text: During the past year, have you been unable to remember what happened the night before because you had been drinking?

options.display: No|Yes, but not in the last year|Yes, during the last year

item.text: Have you or someone else been injured as a result of your drinking?

options.display: No|Yes, but not in the last year|Yes, during the last year

item.text: Has a relative or friend, doctor or other health worker been concerned about your drinking or suggested you cut down?

Scoring the AUDIT Scores for each question range from 0 to 4, with the first response for each question (eg never) scoring 0, the second (eg less than monthly) scoring 1, the third (eg monthly) scoring 2, the fourth (eg weekly) scoring 3, and the last response (eg. daily or almost daily) scoring 4. For questions 9 and 10, which only have three responses, the scoring is 0, 2 and 4 (from left to right). A score of 8 or more is associated with harmful or hazardous drinking, a score of 13 or more in women, and 15 or more in men, is likely to indicate alcohol dependence.

The Alcohol Use Disorders Identification Test: Self-Report Version Because alcohol use can affect your health and can interfere with certain medications and treatments, it is important that we ask some questions about your use of alcohol. Your answers will remain confidential so please be honest. Place an X in one box that best describes your answer to each question.
